<subSubSection pageId="176" pageNumber="177" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="176.[151,1437,151,1725]" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1519,1545]" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species (noun in apposition) is derrived from the combined Greek prefix ‘ 
<emphasis box="[161,214,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">para</emphasis>
-’ (close by) and the species name 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Brenske" authorityYear="1897" box="[599,681,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Autoserica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="detersa">
<emphasis box="[599,681,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">detersa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with reference to the similarity to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Brenske" authorityYear="1897" box="[1070,1189,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Autoserica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="176" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="detersa">
<emphasis box="[1070,1189,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="176" pageNumber="177">M. detersa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(adjective in nominative singular).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
